Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 21:30:32 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?fix:=20student/parent=20attendance=20date=20now?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20renders=20(was=20'=E2=80=94'=20on=20mobile)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Attendance.date intentionally has no Eloquent cast (kept raw 'Y-m-d'
so date = ? lookups don't break, see comment on the model). That meant
\$r->date was a string, and optional(\$string)->format() returns null
because strings have no format() method — so the mobile parent &
student attendance screens received date: null and rendered '—'.

Now parses via Carbon::parse(\$r->date)->format(\$dateFmt) before
returning. Teacher branch (StaffAttendance) already worked because
that model has a date cast.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 app/Http/Controllers/Api/MobileApiController.php | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/app/Http/Controllers/Api/MobileApiController.php b/app/Http/Controllers/Api/MobileApiController.php
index 2d79363..e8bf132 100644
--- a/app/Http/Controllers/Api/MobileApiController.php
+++ b/app/Http/Controllers/Api/MobileApiController.php
@@ -564,7 +564,9 @@ public function attendance(Request $request): JsonResponse
         return response()->json([
             'summary'    => $summary,
             'records'    => $records->map(fn($r) => [
-                'date'    => optional($r->date)->format($dateFmt),
+                // Attendance.date has no Eloquent cast (kept as raw "Y-m-d" so
+                // WHERE date = … lookups work), so parse before formatting.
+                'date'    => $r->date ? Carbon::parse($r->date)->format($dateFmt) : null,
                 'status'  => $r->status,
                 'remarks' => $r->remarks,
             ]),
